{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "The [[4, 1, 2]] code is prepared in a fault-tolerant manner by initializing the data qubits in the |+〉 state and then measuring each of the Pauli-Z-type stabilizer operators Z 4 Z 6 and Z 15 Z 17.",
    "These measurements can be facilitated with the ancillary qubits 5 and 16, respectively.",
    "Each of these operators is measured twice such that we can detect a single measurement error during preparation (see also ref.",
    "4).We transfer a single logical qubit of the [[4, 2, 2]] code onto the [ [4, 1, 2]] code using logical measurements.",
    "In step 3, we perform a weight-4 measurement that measures the parity of two logical qubits over the two codes."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The [[4, 1, 2]] code is prepared in a fault-tolerant manner by initializing the data qubits in the |+〉 state and then measuring each of the Pauli-Z-type stabilizer operators Z 4 Z 6 and Z 15 Z 17.",
    "4).We transfer a single logical qubit of the [[4, 2, 2]] code onto the [ [4, 1, 2]] code using logical measurements."
  ]
